Step 1: Identify the relevant data.
• Initial Current Assets = 8,000,000.00 (from balance sheet at 2023-12-31)
• Ending Current Assets = 11,364,912.39 (from balance sheet at 2024-02-04)
• Main Business Revenue = 851,679.79 (from income statement at 2024-02-04)

Step 2: Compute the Average Current Assets.
  Average Current Assets = (Initial Current Assets + Ending Current Assets) / 2
    = (8,000,000.00 + 11,364,912.39) / 2
    = 19,364,912.39 / 2
    ≈ 9,682,456.20

Step 3: Calculate the Current Assets Turnover Ratio.
  Current Assets Turnover Ratio = Main Business Revenue / Average Current Assets
    ≈ 851,679.79 / 9,682,456.20
    ≈ 0.0879

Rounding to two decimal places, the ratio is approximately 0.09.

Thus, the final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Current Assets Turnover Ratio": "0.09"
  }
}
